WEBVTT

00:01.521 --> 00:05.023
===MUTANT X Crossroads Of The Soul / s02.ep07===

00:09.209 --> 00:10.410
I GOT A WICKED DEAL.

00:10.410 --> 00:12.012
'78 CAMARO,
45,000 ORIGINAL MILES.

00:12.012 --> 00:13.613
GUY WANTED FIFTEEN G'S.

00:13.613 --> 00:15.215
I GOT HIM DOWN TO THIRTEEN-FIVE.

00:15.215 --> 00:16.416
HMM.

00:16.416 --> 00:17.617
THREE-FIFTY LT-1 ENGINE?

00:17.617 --> 00:19.219
YEAH, BABY, THE REAL DEAL.

00:19.219 --> 00:21.221
BOOK SAYS
THERE'S ONLY A THOUSAND
OF THEM IN EXISTENCE,

00:21.221 --> 00:22.422
AND THIS IS ONE OF THEM.

00:22.422 --> 00:24.824
EVEN CAME WITH ITS OWN
DANCING HULA GIRL ON THE DASH.

00:28.828 --> 00:30.830
YEAH, BRENNAN, AS HAPPY AS
WE ARE YOU'VE MANAGED TO SAVE A

00:30.830 --> 00:32.832
HUNK OF METAL FROM THE SCRAP
HEAP, THE REST OF US HAVE SPENT

00:33.233 --> 00:35.235
THE LAST TWELVE HOURS DOWN AT
THE DOCKS TRYING TO TRACK DOWN

00:35.235 --> 00:36.836
A SHIPMENT OF
STOLEN MEDICAL SUPPLIES.

00:36.836 --> 00:39.239
I GUESS THAT MEANS
YOU DIDN'T FIND IT.

00:39.239 --> 00:41.241
DON'T EVEN START.

00:43.243 --> 00:44.844
ALL RIGHT, GUYS. YOU KNOW WHAT?

00:45.245 --> 00:46.846
THIS STORM'S COMING IN PRETTY
HARD AND MY CONNECTION'S GOING

00:46.846 --> 00:48.848
BAD ANYWAY, SO I'LL CALL
YOU WHEN I GET CLOSER TO TOWN.

00:48.848 --> 00:50.850
CONNECTION'S GOING?

00:50.850 --> 00:52.052
PLEASE.

00:52.052 --> 00:54.854
AND HE USED TO BE A CON MAN?

00:56.000 --> 01:02.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:36.896 --> 01:39.699
GUESS IT WASN'T SUCH
A GOOD DEAL AFTER ALL.

02:21.741 --> 02:23.343
I AM ADAM KANE.

02:23.343 --> 02:26.146
I WAS A PIONEER
OF GENETIC RESEARCH,

02:26.146 --> 02:29.349
MANIPULATING DNA
TO SAVE HUMAN LIVES.

02:29.349 --> 02:35.355
BUT IN MANY THEIR
GENES UNEXPECTEDLY MUTATED

02:35.755 --> 02:38.158
AND DEVELOPED
SUPERHUMAN ABILITIES.

03:04.584 --> 03:06.986
TOGETHER WITH FOUR OF THE MOST
POWERFUL I FIGHT TO PROTECT A

03:07.387 --> 03:09.789
WORLD THAT DOESN'T
EVEN KNOW WE EXIST.

03:13.393 --> 03:14.594
WE ARE...

03:14.594 --> 03:16.996
MUTANT X.

03:20.166 --> 03:26.573
SHH... SHH... IT'S OKAY.

03:26.573 --> 03:30.577
UHHH... UHHH.

03:30.977 --> 03:32.979
SHH. SHH, DON'T TALK.

03:33.379 --> 03:37.784
I'LL MAKE IT ALL BETTER...

03:48.194 --> 03:50.597
YOU KNOW, IF THESE GUYS ARE
PLANNING ON SHIPPING THE STOLEN

03:50.597 --> 03:54.200
EQUIPMENT OUT OF THE PORT, THEY
GOTTA BE HIDING IT SOME PLACE.

03:54.200 --> 03:57.403
YEAH, LIKE ANY ONE OF,
OH MAYBE, A THOUSAND RUN-DOWN

03:57.403 --> 03:59.806
WAREHOUSES THAT WE'LL
NEVER HAVE TIME TO SEARCH.

04:00.206 --> 04:01.808
SOMEONE ON THE STREET MUST KNOW.

04:01.808 --> 04:03.810
IT'S AN UNDERCOVER JOB.

04:03.810 --> 04:05.011
NO, IT'S A BRENNAN JOB,

04:05.011 --> 04:07.013
AND HE'S OFF SCREWING
AROUND WITH HIS HOTROD.

04:07.013 --> 04:09.015
LET ME SEE IF I CAN GET AN ETA.

04:09.015 --> 04:16.623
BRENNAN. BRENNAN, DO YOU COPY?

04:17.023 --> 04:19.425
I HOPE HE'S OKAY.

04:19.425 --> 04:21.427
I MEAN, HE SAID THAT THERE
WAS A STORM COMING AND WHO KNOWS

04:21.427 --> 04:23.830
WHAT KIND OF CONDITION
THAT CAR WAS IN.

04:23.830 --> 04:26.232
OKAY.

04:26.633 --> 04:29.435
CAN WE TALK SOME MORE
LIKELY SCENARIOS FOR A SECOND.

04:29.435 --> 04:31.838
WHITE TRASH CAMARO...

04:32.238 --> 04:35.041
BRENNAN...

04:35.041 --> 04:37.443
MAYBE A SMALL-TOWN WAITRESS WITH
A TASTE FOR BOTH OF THE ABOVE?

04:37.443 --> 04:40.246
IF YOU ASK ME, HE'S PROBABLY
JUST SHACKED UP IN A NO-TELL

04:40.246 --> 04:45.051
MOTEL USING HIS, "I THINK
WE HAVE SOME ELECTRICITY
BETWEEN US" LINE.

04:45.051 --> 04:46.653
NO.

04:46.653 --> 04:49.055
NO, IF SOMETHING HELD HIM UP
THEN HE WOULD'VE CONTACTED US.

04:49.055 --> 04:51.457
WELL, I'LL KEEP A TRACE RUNNING.

04:51.457 --> 04:53.059
IF HIS COMLINK'S PUTTING
OUT ANYTHING AT ALL WE SHOULD BE

04:53.059 --> 04:55.461
ABLE TO FIND HIM.

05:07.473 --> 05:10.677
THERE WAS... AN ACCIDENT.

05:10.677 --> 05:12.278
THIS TRUCK WAS
HEADING TOWARDS MY CAR.

05:12.278 --> 05:13.880
SHH. IT'S OKAY.

05:13.880 --> 05:15.481
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

05:15.481 --> 05:19.085
THANKS FOR TAKING
CARE OF ME LIKE THIS.

05:19.085 --> 05:21.087
MY NAME IS MIRANDA.

05:21.087 --> 05:23.489
BRENNAN MULWRAY.

05:29.095 --> 05:32.298
DID YOU PUT
MY CLOTHES SOMEWHERE?

05:32.298 --> 05:34.300
THEY WERE RUINED IN THE STORM.

05:34.300 --> 05:39.105
BUT, I HAVE OTHERS FOR YOU.

05:39.105 --> 05:41.107
THANKS.

05:41.107 --> 05:45.111
AND I FOUND THIS IN YOUR POCKET.

05:52.318 --> 05:53.519
UM...

05:59.125 --> 06:00.326
THERE.

06:00.326 --> 06:02.328
BRENNAN LAST CHECKED IN AT 9:18.

06:02.328 --> 06:05.932
HE WAS... HERE.

06:05.932 --> 06:08.334
THIRTY MILES
OUTSIDE OF EDGARSTOWN.

06:08.735 --> 06:11.137
SO IF HE HAD CAR TROUBLES
OR HAD TO GET IN FROM THE STORM,

06:11.537 --> 06:13.539
I FIGURE THAT'S WHERE
HE WOULD'VE WOUND UP.

06:13.539 --> 06:16.342
YEAH,
BUT A STORM DOESN'T EXPLAIN
WHY HIS COMLINK DIDN'T WORK.

06:16.342 --> 06:17.944
I SAY WE GO FIND HIM.

06:18.344 --> 06:21.147
WHY DON'T YOU GRAB EMMA,
GRAB SHALIMAR, GET ON THE ROAD?

06:21.147 --> 06:22.749
I THINK YOU'LL WANT
TO RETRACE HIS ROUTE ALL

06:23.149 --> 06:26.753
THE WAY DOWN INTO EDGARSTOWN.

06:28.354 --> 06:32.358
ADAM. ADAM.

06:32.358 --> 06:35.561
HEY, JESS, CAN ANYONE HEAR ME?

06:43.569 --> 06:46.773
WELL, I DON'T
KNOW IF YOUR DAD'S STYLE
QUITE WORKS FOR ME, BUT...

06:46.773 --> 06:48.374
HERE IT IS.

06:48.775 --> 06:50.376
I THINK YOU LOOK GREAT.

06:50.376 --> 06:52.779
NOW, I JUST HAVE
TO FIGURE OUT WHO YOU ARE AND

06:52.779 --> 06:54.781
HOW COME I'VE NEVER
SEEN YOU AROUND BEFORE.

06:54.781 --> 06:57.183
YEAH, WELL, I TOLD YOU,
I'M NOT FROM AROUND HERE.

06:57.183 --> 06:59.585
I KNOW WHAT YOU
SAID, BUT YOU'RE WRONG.

06:59.986 --> 07:03.589
LOOK, MIRANDA, THERE'S
PEOPLE THAT ARE GOING TO BE

07:03.589 --> 07:07.193
WORRIED ABOUT ME SO IS THERE
A PHONE AROUND HERE SOMEWHERE?

07:07.193 --> 07:08.394
A PHONE.

07:08.394 --> 07:10.396
UM, I THINK THERE'S
ONE AT BRADY'S STORE.

07:10.396 --> 07:11.998
WANT TO GO?

07:11.998 --> 07:15.601
LET'S GO.

07:24.010 --> 07:25.611
WHERE ARE ALL THE CARS, THEN?

07:25.611 --> 07:26.813
CARS?

07:27.213 --> 07:28.414
YEAH, YOU KNOW, FOUR WHEELS...

07:28.815 --> 07:31.217
VROOM VROOM?

07:32.819 --> 07:34.020
HI, MIRANDA.

07:34.020 --> 07:35.621
HI, EVERYBODY.

07:35.621 --> 07:38.424
THIS IS BEN
GILBERT, GERALD'S SON.

07:38.424 --> 07:41.627
BEN GILBERT?

07:41.627 --> 07:43.229
HI.

07:43.229 --> 07:44.831
I'LL TELL YOU LATER.

07:44.831 --> 07:46.432
HUH.

07:46.432 --> 07:47.633
LET'S GO GET SOME ICED TEA.

07:47.633 --> 07:48.835
YEAH, YOU KNOW WHAT?

07:48.835 --> 07:50.036
ORDER ME ONE.

07:50.436 --> 07:51.237
I'M GOING TO MAKE A CALL.

07:51.637 --> 07:53.239
BE RIGHT BACK.

07:54.040 --> 07:57.643
HOW YOU DOIN'?

07:59.245 --> 08:02.448
LUCIAN, LET THAT BOY THROUGH.

08:04.050 --> 08:06.052
HEY, LOOK, I DON'T MIND
TELLING YOU THAT GIRL THERE,

08:06.452 --> 08:08.054
SHE'S SPOKEN FOR.

08:08.054 --> 08:09.655
ANYONE TELL HER THAT?

08:09.655 --> 08:10.857
I'M TELLING YOU.

08:10.857 --> 08:12.058
SHE'S MINE.

08:12.458 --> 08:13.659
YOU KNOW, I DON'T
HAVE TIME FOR THIS.

08:14.060 --> 08:15.261
DON'T START SOMETHING
YOU CAN'T FINISH.

08:15.261 --> 08:17.263
HOW'S EVERYBODY TODAY?

08:17.263 --> 08:20.066
WE'RE GOOD, ZANDER, REAL GOOD.

08:20.066 --> 08:22.869
THAT'S HOW IT SHOULD BE.

08:22.869 --> 08:25.271
I UNDERSTAND THERE'S
A CONSTRUCTION PROJECT OVER

08:25.271 --> 08:27.273
AT ANNIE'S YOU'RE
SUPPOSED TO BE AT, JOSH.

08:27.673 --> 08:30.476
YEAH.

08:30.476 --> 08:34.080
WE'LL TALK AGAIN.

08:34.080 --> 08:35.681
LET'S GO.

08:45.291 --> 08:47.693
SO YOU'RE BEN GILBERT?

08:48.094 --> 08:50.496
UH, YEAH.

08:50.496 --> 08:55.301
ARE YOU GOING BACK TO THE
FARM OR YOU PLANNING TO STAY?

08:55.301 --> 08:58.104
YOU KNOW, I HAVEN'T DECIDED YET.

08:58.504 --> 09:00.506
TOWN'S REAL FRIENDLY, THOUGH.

09:00.506 --> 09:04.510
ANYTHING ELSE?

09:04.911 --> 09:06.913
NOT RIGHT NOW.

09:06.913 --> 09:08.114
HAVE A GOOD DAY.

09:08.114 --> 09:10.516
YOU TOO.

09:24.130 --> 09:25.731
OPERATOR, CAN I HELP YOU?

09:26.132 --> 09:28.935
UH, YEAH, OPERATOR,
I'D LIKE TO MAKE A
LONG DISTANCE COLLECT CALL.

09:28.935 --> 09:30.937
754-245...

09:31.337 --> 09:33.339
I'M SORRY, THAT
EXCHANGE DOES NOT EXIST.

09:33.339 --> 09:34.941
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

09:34.941 --> 09:36.542
I CALL IT EVERY DAY.

09:36.542 --> 09:38.144
THAT EXCHANGE
DOES NOT EXIST, SIR.

09:38.144 --> 09:41.747
PLEASE CHECK YOUR
NUMBER AND CALL AGAIN.

09:49.755 --> 09:52.959
YOUR TOWN IS SERIOUSLY WHACKED.

09:52.959 --> 09:55.361
I KNEW YOU'D COME AROUND.

09:55.361 --> 09:58.164
YEAH.

10:08.174 --> 10:10.176
THAT WAS NICE.

10:10.176 --> 10:12.578
OKAY, SO TELL ME WHAT THIS
BEN GILBERT THING IS ABOUT NOW.

10:12.578 --> 10:15.781
GERALD GILBERT AND HIS
BOYS LIVE ON THE EDGE OF TOWN.

10:16.182 --> 10:18.184
THEY HAVEN'T
BEEN AROUND FOR YEARS.

10:18.184 --> 10:19.785
OKAY, SO WHY DON'T YOU
JUST TELL THEM WHO I REALLY AM?

10:19.785 --> 10:20.987
I COULDN'T.

10:20.987 --> 10:23.789
I WOULDN'T WANT THEM
TO THINK THAT YOU WERE CRAZY.

10:23.789 --> 10:24.991
I'M OUTTA HERE.

10:24.991 --> 10:26.993
LISTEN, I KNOW THAT YOU
THINK THAT YOU'RE NOT FROM HERE,

10:27.393 --> 10:28.594
BUT THERE'S NOWHERE ELSE.

10:28.995 --> 10:31.397
PEOPLE CAN'T GO BEYOND THE WALL.

10:31.397 --> 10:33.399
WHAT WALL?

10:33.399 --> 10:34.600
ON EIGHTH STREET.

10:34.600 --> 10:37.803
IT'S THE END OF THE WORLD.

10:47.013 --> 10:51.417
WAIT! STOP!

10:53.019 --> 10:55.021
BEN!

11:03.029 --> 11:05.431
OHHH!

11:11.037 --> 11:12.238
MY POWER'S NOT WORKING.

11:12.238 --> 11:14.640
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

11:15.041 --> 11:17.043
TRYING TO GET OUT OF HERE.

11:17.443 --> 11:18.244
WHY?

11:18.244 --> 11:19.445
WE'RE HAPPY HERE.

11:19.845 --> 11:21.447
BRENNAN, NO!

11:21.447 --> 11:23.449
HUH... UH...

11:23.449 --> 11:25.851
AGHHH!

11:27.853 --> 11:29.455
NOW YOU KNOW?

11:29.855 --> 11:31.457
NOW YOU BELIEVE ME?

11:31.857 --> 11:33.459
THERE'S ONLY NEW HOPE.

11:33.459 --> 11:36.262
THERE'S ONLY
YOU AND ME -- TOGETHER.

11:46.205 --> 11:47.406
COME AWAY FROM IT.

11:47.406 --> 11:49.008
THERE'S NOTHING
ON THE OTHER SIDE.

11:49.008 --> 11:50.209
BRENNAN, IT'S THE END.

11:50.609 --> 11:51.811
NO, IT'S NOT.

11:51.811 --> 11:53.412
IT'S A FORCE FIELD, OR...

11:53.412 --> 11:55.014
I DON'T KNOW.

11:55.014 --> 11:58.217
THERE'S GOTTA BE A...

11:58.217 --> 12:01.020
SOME KIND OF PROJECTION
FROM THE INSIDE,

12:01.020 --> 12:02.621
BECAUSE YOU
CAN'T SEE ANYTHING...

12:02.621 --> 12:04.623
CARS, OR PLANES, NOTHING.

12:04.623 --> 12:07.426
TELL YOU WHAT,
IF I HAD MY POWERS I'D
JUST BLAST A HOLE THROUGH.

12:07.426 --> 12:08.627
YOU'D SEE FOR YOURSELF.

12:09.028 --> 12:09.829
POWERS?

12:09.829 --> 12:11.831
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

12:11.831 --> 12:13.833
THIS BARRIER
IS NOT NATURAL, OKAY?

12:13.833 --> 12:15.835
SOMEBODY PUT IT HERE
TO KEEP THIS TOWN INSIDE.

12:15.835 --> 12:17.436
DON'T SAY THAT.

12:17.436 --> 12:19.038
IT HAS ALWAYS BEEN HERE.

12:19.038 --> 12:20.639
YOU HAVE TO BELIEVE.

12:20.639 --> 12:22.241
WHY DO I HAVE TO BELIEVE, HUH?

12:22.641 --> 12:23.442
I HAVE A LIFE OUT THERE.

12:23.843 --> 12:25.444
I HAVE FRIENDS THAT
I WANT TO GET BACK TO.

12:25.444 --> 12:27.446
I'M GETTING OUT OF THIS TOWN.

12:27.446 --> 12:28.647
WAIT!

12:33.853 --> 12:35.855
MIRANDA.

12:35.855 --> 12:37.456
I WASN'T YELLING AT YOU.

12:37.456 --> 12:41.460
I'M FRUSTRATED, OKAY?

12:47.867 --> 12:50.669
I DIDN'T MEAN TO MAKE YOU CRY.

12:50.669 --> 12:53.072
COME ON.

12:53.472 --> 12:55.875
I JUST REALLY
NEED YOU TO BELIEVE.

12:56.275 --> 12:58.677
I DON'T WANT YOU TO DISAPPEAR.

12:58.677 --> 13:02.281
LOOK AT ME.

13:08.287 --> 13:10.689
I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

13:11.090 --> 13:15.494
NOT FOR NOW, ANYWAY.

13:21.100 --> 13:24.303
JOSH, WE'RE SUPPOSED TO
BE AT THE CONSTRUCTION PROJECT.

13:24.703 --> 13:25.905
WELL, WE GOT
SOMETHING TO DO FIRST.

13:26.305 --> 13:27.506
COME ON.

13:27.506 --> 13:31.510
GONNA PAY A LITTLE HOUSE
CALL TO BEN GILBERT'S FATHER.

13:37.917 --> 13:39.919
WELL, I DON'T KNOW
WHERE ELSE TO CHECK.

13:39.919 --> 13:41.520
I MEAN, WE'VE ASKED AT
THE COFFEE SHOP, THE MOTEL...

13:41.921 --> 13:45.524
WELL, IT'S A STRAIGHT SHOT ON
ROUTE 17 FROM EDGARSTOWN TO US.

13:45.524 --> 13:47.526
HE HAD TO COME THROUGH
HERE AND HE HAD TO HAVE STOPPED.

13:47.927 --> 13:51.530
WELL, HE DIDN'T JUST DISAPPEAR.

13:56.735 --> 13:58.737
MAYBE HE STOPPED FOR PARTS.

13:58.737 --> 13:59.939
ALL RIGHT.

13:59.939 --> 14:01.540
YOU CHECK IT OUT.

14:01.540 --> 14:03.542
WE'LL HEAD TO THE
POLICE STATION I MEAN,

14:03.542 --> 14:05.945
SOMEBODY'S GOT TO HAVE SEEN HIM.

14:05.945 --> 14:08.347
DON'T LEAVE ME HERE.

14:15.554 --> 14:16.755
HO, HO.

14:16.755 --> 14:18.357
WHOA.

14:18.357 --> 14:20.759
NEED TO TALK TO YOU, OLD MAN.

14:20.759 --> 14:23.162
YOU'RE A MARCUS, AREN'T YOU?

14:23.562 --> 14:25.164
YOU HAVE THAT LOOK.

14:25.164 --> 14:27.166
WELL, YOU'RE LOOKING AT
THE FUTURE HEAD OF TOWN COUNCIL.

14:27.166 --> 14:29.168
THAT SO?

14:29.168 --> 14:32.371
I HAD A FEELING THIS TOWN WAS
HEADING IN THE WRONG DIRECTION.

14:32.771 --> 14:33.973
I GUESS THERE'S PROOF.

14:33.973 --> 14:35.174
HEY, HEY!

14:35.574 --> 14:37.576
YOU SOUND LIKE A MAN
WHO'S FORGOTTEN HOW TO BELIEVE.

14:37.576 --> 14:38.777
THAT CAN BE DANGEROUS.

14:39.178 --> 14:41.180
I BELIEVE
THE IDEALS YOUR GRANDFATHER
FOUNDED THIS PLACE ON.

14:41.580 --> 14:43.582
ALL THAT'S LEFT
NOW ARE THE WORDS.

14:43.582 --> 14:45.184
WELL, YOU'D DO WELL TO
LISTEN TO THOSE WORDS, OLD MAN,

14:45.584 --> 14:48.387
AND KEEP YOUR SON OUT
OF TOWN AND AWAY FROM MIRANDA,

14:48.387 --> 14:49.588
YOU UNDERSTAND ME?

14:49.588 --> 14:51.190
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

14:51.590 --> 14:55.194
MY SONS HAVEN'T
BEEN IN TOWN IN YEARS.

14:55.194 --> 14:59.198
IS THAT BEN?
-YES.

14:59.598 --> 15:04.003
WHY? WHAT DO YOU WANT WITH US?

15:04.003 --> 15:06.805
WELL, WE'LL BE BACK TO DISCUSS
THAT WITH YOU, MR. GILBERT.

15:06.805 --> 15:08.407
YOU CAN COUNT ON THAT.

15:08.407 --> 15:10.809
LET'S GO. LET'S GO.

15:15.614 --> 15:17.616
LOOK, HAVE THERE BEEN ANY
ACCIDENTS REPORTED IN THE LAST

15:18.017 --> 15:19.618
TWENTY-FOUR HOURS
INVOLVING A CAMARO?

15:19.618 --> 15:21.220
NOT... NOT A ONE.

15:21.220 --> 15:23.622
WELL, OUR FRIEND'S DISAPPEARED
SOMEWHERE BETWEEN HERE AND

15:23.622 --> 15:25.224
THIRTY MILES WEST ON ROUTE 17.

15:25.624 --> 15:26.825
YOU KNOW ANYTHING ABOUT THAT?

15:26.825 --> 15:28.427
LOOK. I GOT WORK TO DO.

15:28.427 --> 15:29.628
I'M ALONE HERE.

15:30.029 --> 15:32.031
SORRY, I CAN'T HELP YOU.

15:38.437 --> 15:39.638
WE'RE ALL THE SAME HERE.

15:39.638 --> 15:40.839
YOU'RE NO DIFFERENT.

15:40.839 --> 15:42.841
YEAH?

15:42.841 --> 15:44.843
MAYBE HERE.

15:44.843 --> 15:47.646
SO WHAT'S IT LIKE BEING
LIKE EVERYONE ELSE, ANYWAY?

15:47.646 --> 15:49.648
IT'S NICE.

15:49.648 --> 15:52.451
THERE'S TIME FOR LYING
IN THE SUN, FOR WALKING,

15:52.451 --> 15:55.654
FOR BEING WITH FRIENDS.

15:56.055 --> 15:57.656
ESPECIALLY THE
ONES THAT YOU LOVE.

15:58.057 --> 16:02.061
HMM...

16:02.061 --> 16:04.463
WELL, I GOTTA TELL YOU,
NEW HOPE IS BECOMING MORE

16:04.463 --> 16:06.865
APPEALING BY THE MINUTE.

16:06.865 --> 16:08.867
I KNEW YOU'D LOVE IT... BEN.

16:13.272 --> 16:17.676
WHAT WOULD YOU DO WITHOUT ME?

16:21.280 --> 16:22.481
OH, IF I DIDN'T
HAVE MY LIFE OUT THERE,

16:22.881 --> 16:24.483
I COULD SEE SETTLING
DOWN IN A PLACE LIKE THIS.

16:24.483 --> 16:26.485
YOU MEAN IT?

16:26.485 --> 16:28.487
YEAH, IT DEFINITELY
HAS ITS CHARMS.

16:28.487 --> 16:30.889
WELL, THEN, I'LL LET
YOU IN ON A LITTLE SECRET.

16:30.889 --> 16:32.491
REALLY?

16:32.491 --> 16:34.893
I HALF BELIEVE YOU
ARE WHAT YOU SAY YOU ARE,

16:34.893 --> 16:39.698
AN OUTSIDER, BUT
SINCE YOU DON'T EXIST,

16:39.698 --> 16:48.107
THEN THAT MEANS
I'M IN LOVE WITH AN ANGEL.

16:54.913 --> 16:56.915
I WISH WE AT LEAST
HAD A LICENSE PLACE TO TRACE.

16:56.915 --> 16:58.517
HE DIDN'T LEAVE
US MUCH TO GO ON.

17:04.522 --> 17:06.125
THIS IS IT.

17:06.125 --> 17:08.527
OH, MY GOD.

17:19.338 --> 17:23.342
LOOKS LIKE THIS TRUCK
DIDN'T DO TOO WELL, EITHER.

17:32.951 --> 17:34.953
NICE.

17:34.953 --> 17:37.356
EDGARSTOWN TRUCKING
AND JUNK YARD.

17:37.356 --> 17:40.959
THE TRUCK IS THEIRS.

17:43.762 --> 17:45.764
YOU KNOW, I WAS THINKING,

17:45.764 --> 17:48.967
