29:33.371 --> 29:35.774
YES.

29:35.774 --> 29:37.776
OH WAIT, NO, NO, NO.

29:37.776 --> 29:39.377
SOMEONE TOOK THAT FROM ME!

29:39.377 --> 29:41.379
SOMEONE'S TRYING TO SET ME UP.

29:41.379 --> 29:44.983
GERALD.

29:44.983 --> 29:51.790
APPRECIATE YOU COMING DOWN.

29:51.790 --> 29:53.792
YEAH.

29:54.192 --> 29:55.794
SO, WE'LL MAKE THIS QUICK.

29:55.794 --> 29:58.596
DO YOU RECOGNIZE THIS MAN?

29:58.997 --> 30:02.600
THAT'S MY SON, BEN.

30:03.001 --> 30:05.403
WHAT?

30:05.403 --> 30:07.806
THAT'S NOT THE TRUTH.

30:07.806 --> 30:09.407
THAT'S NOT TRUE.

30:09.407 --> 30:11.009
LISTEN TO ME, THAT IS NOT TRUE.

30:11.409 --> 30:13.411
I'VE NEVER SEEN THIS
MAN BEFORE IN MY LIFE!

30:13.411 --> 30:15.013
ENOUGH!

30:15.013 --> 30:18.216
WE'LL RECONVENE IN FIVE MINUTES.

30:18.216 --> 30:19.818
LISTEN TO ME.

30:19.818 --> 30:23.021
I'M TELLING THE TRUTH.

30:28.626 --> 30:31.029
YOU DID THE RIGHT THING, GERALD.

30:31.029 --> 30:36.234
JUST LEAVE MY FAMILY ALONE.

30:37.435 --> 30:38.636
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

30:38.636 --> 30:39.838
HEY...

30:40.238 --> 30:46.644
REMEMBER, OLD
MAN, OUR DAY'S COMING.

30:49.447 --> 30:51.449
YOU ASK ME, THAT LADY AT THE
JUNK YARD WAS HOLDING OUT ON US.

30:51.449 --> 30:53.051
NO, SHE WASN'T.

30:53.451 --> 30:54.652
TRUST ME.

30:54.652 --> 30:57.055
WELL, HE COULDN'T HAVE
JUST DISAPPEARED INTO THIN AIR,

30:57.455 --> 30:58.656
COULD HE?

31:02.660 --> 31:05.463
MAYBE THE AIR'S
NOT SO THIN AFTER ALL.

31:17.475 --> 31:19.878
UH... UGH!

31:20.678 --> 31:23.081
WHAT THE HELL WAS THAT?

31:23.481 --> 31:25.083
I'D SAY THAT'S ADAM'S BUBBLE.

31:25.083 --> 31:27.085
THE SATELLITE IMAGERY THAT
I'M PICKING UP OVER THE AREA

31:27.485 --> 31:30.288
IS DISTORTED BY
A POWERFUL ENERGY FIELD.

31:30.288 --> 31:31.489
WE KNOW.

31:31.489 --> 31:33.892
SHALIMAR JUST HIT THE GLASS
CEILING TRYING TO FIND A WAY IN.

31:34.292 --> 31:36.694
SO I GUESS SOMEWHERE IN
THERE IS ALFRED MARCUS'S LITTLE

31:36.694 --> 31:38.696
SLICE OF HEAVEN.

31:38.696 --> 31:40.698
BRENNAN MUST'VE FOUND A WAY IN.

31:41.099 --> 31:43.902
WELL, THEN WE GOTTA
FIND A WAY TO GET HIM OUT.

31:43.902 --> 31:45.904
YOU GUYS STAY RIGHT THERE.

31:45.904 --> 31:48.706
I THINK I MIGHT'VE
JUST FIGURED OUT A WAY
TO CRACK THROUGH THE SHIELD.

31:48.706 --> 31:50.708
I'M ON MY WAY.

31:50.708 --> 31:51.910
COPY THAT, ADAM.

31:51.910 --> 31:55.113
WE'LL WAIT FOR YOU HERE.

31:55.113 --> 31:57.916
WE CAN'T ABANDON EVERYTHING
BECAUSE OF ONE OUTSIDER.

31:58.316 --> 32:00.718
WE MUST ENSURE HARMONY.

32:00.718 --> 32:03.922
WE'RE DOING THE RIGHT THING.

32:03.922 --> 32:05.924
PERHAPS.

32:05.924 --> 32:09.928
BUT HOW MANY
TIMES DO WE HAVE TO KILL THE
TRUTH BEFORE IT STAYS DEAD?

32:09.928 --> 32:15.133
BEN GILBERT, BECAUSE YOU FAILED
TO ACCEPT RESPONSIBILITY AND

32:15.133 --> 32:19.137
REMORSE FOR THE MURDER OF
ZANDER DELASSANDRO AND CHOSE TO

32:19.537 --> 32:23.942
HIDE BEHIND LIES AND FANTASY,
BLASPHEMING THE FOUNDATIONS OF

32:23.942 --> 32:28.346
NEW HOPE, WE HAVE NO
CHOICE BUT TO FIND YOU GUILTY.

32:28.346 --> 32:35.153
THEREFORE, ON THIS DAY,
YOU WILL BE PUT TO DEATH IN TOWN

32:35.153 --> 32:42.760
SQUARE, IN FRONT
OF THE ASSEMBLED CITIZENS.

32:46.764 --> 32:49.968
HUH...!

33:09.187 --> 33:10.388
YOU CAN'T DO THIS.

33:10.388 --> 33:11.990
I DIDN'T KILL ZANDER!

33:11.990 --> 33:13.591
YOU HAVE TO LISTEN TO ME!

33:13.591 --> 33:15.593
YOU'RE ABOUT TO TAKE
YOUR LAST BREATH, MR. GILBERT.

33:15.593 --> 33:16.794
MAKE IT A GOOD SHOW.

33:16.794 --> 33:17.996
MY NAME'S NOT BEN GILBERT.

33:17.996 --> 33:19.197
IT'S NOT BEN GILBERT!

33:19.597 --> 33:20.798
IT'S BRENNAN MULWRAY.

33:21.199 --> 33:23.201
IN A FEW MINUTES,
IT WON'T MATTER WHAT
THE HELL YOUR NAME IS.

33:23.201 --> 33:24.402
I DIDN'T DO IT!

33:24.402 --> 33:25.603
YOU GOTTA LISTEN TO ME!

33:25.603 --> 33:26.804
I DIDN'T DO IT!

33:26.804 --> 33:28.406
LET'S GET THIS OVER WITH.

33:28.806 --> 33:30.008
MY NAME'S NOT BEN GILBERT.

33:30.008 --> 33:32.410
I DIDN'T DO IT!

33:34.412 --> 33:35.613
HEY, ADAM?

33:35.613 --> 33:36.814
ALMOST READY WITH THE PAYLOAD.

33:38.416 --> 33:40.018
NOW, THE NIGHT THAT BRENNAN
DISAPPEARED, I FOUND OUT THAT

33:40.418 --> 33:42.820
THERE WAS A LIGHTNING STORM
THAT MAY HAVE DESTABILIZED THE

33:42.820 --> 33:45.223
DOME LONG ENOUGH
FOR HIM TO SLIP THROUGH.

33:45.223 --> 33:47.225
YEAH, WE CAN'T EXACTLY
WAIT FOR ANOTHER STORM.

33:47.225 --> 33:49.227
NO, EXACTLY, WHICH IS WHY WE'RE
GOING TO GIVE MOTHER NATURE

33:49.227 --> 33:51.629
A LITTLE HELPING HAND
BY SEEDING THE AREA WITH THIS

33:51.629 --> 33:55.233
SUPERCHARGED SILVER IODIDE.

33:55.233 --> 33:56.834
IF THERE'S ANY
ELECTRICITY IN THE AIR,

33:56.834 --> 34:00.438
THAT STUFF IS
GOING TO MAKE IT SIZZLE.

34:00.438 --> 34:02.840
WE'RE ON TARGET
WHENEVER YOU'RE READY.

34:03.241 --> 34:06.444
LET'S BEGIN THE SEEDING.

34:13.251 --> 34:15.253
YOU CAN KILL ME
BUT IT'S NOT GOING TO STOP
THE TRUTH AND YOU KNOW IT.

34:15.253 --> 34:17.655
ALL THOSE PEOPLE THAT YOU THINK
DISAPPEARED WERE MURDERED BY

34:17.655 --> 34:19.657
THE TOWN COUNCIL BECAUSE
THEY CAN'T HANDLE THE TRUTH.

34:19.657 --> 34:22.860
YOU DID A GOOD THING,
TURNING HIM IN, MIRANDA.

34:22.860 --> 34:24.462
YOU'RE ONE OF US.

34:24.462 --> 34:26.864
WE ALL DID WHAT WE HAD TO DO.

34:26.864 --> 34:28.466
YOU DID THE HARD PART, RIGHT?

34:28.466 --> 34:30.068
KILLING ZANDER.

34:30.068 --> 34:31.268
I DIDN'T KILL ANYBODY.

34:31.668 --> 34:32.870
JOSH SAID THAT YOU DID.

34:32.870 --> 34:34.072
WELL, HE'S LYING.

34:34.072 --> 34:35.273
IT WAS HIM.

34:35.273 --> 34:36.474
HE SAID ZANDER DESERVED IT.

34:36.474 --> 34:37.275
WHIP THE HORSES!

34:37.675 --> 34:38.876
DO IT!

34:38.876 --> 34:40.078
HAH!

34:40.478 --> 34:41.679
HAH!

34:41.679 --> 34:43.281
MIRANDA!

34:43.281 --> 34:44.482
AH...!

34:44.482 --> 34:45.683
THIS STOPS NOW!

34:45.683 --> 34:46.884
YOU KILLED ZANDER!

34:46.884 --> 34:47.685
LET HIM GO!

34:47.685 --> 34:48.886
HE'S INNOCENT!

34:48.886 --> 34:51.289
LET HIM GO!

34:51.289 --> 34:52.090
AGGHH!

34:52.489 --> 34:53.291
AGGHH!

34:53.291 --> 34:54.492
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

34:54.492 --> 34:56.094
ENDING THIS HERE AND NOW.

34:56.094 --> 34:58.496
LOOK... LOOK, LET HIM DOWN.

34:58.496 --> 35:00.898
PUT HIM DOWN.

35:00.898 --> 35:03.701
PUT HIM DOWN!

35:04.102 --> 35:07.305
GET ME OUT OF THIS...

35:07.305 --> 35:09.707
THE OUTSIDER IS NOT MY SON!

35:09.707 --> 35:12.910
HE'S THE ONE TELLING THE TRUTH.

35:12.910 --> 35:14.912
THIS PLACE HAS BECOME A PRISON.

35:14.912 --> 35:17.715
I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU'VE BECOME.

35:24.922 --> 35:28.526
UH!

35:28.526 --> 35:37.335
OH... THANKS.

35:38.536 --> 35:40.538
AGH...!

35:44.142 --> 35:45.343
LET'S GO.

35:45.343 --> 35:47.745
COME ON, LET'S GO!

36:00.258 --> 36:02.660
YOU TOOK A BIG
CHANCE HELPING ME BACK THERE.

36:02.660 --> 36:03.861
I DID WHAT WAS RIGHT.

36:04.262 --> 36:05.863
YEAH, WELL, MOST PEOPLE
WOULD'VE HELPED THEMSELVES.

36:05.863 --> 36:07.865
YOU WOULD'VE
DONE THE SAME FOR ME.

36:07.865 --> 36:09.467
I KNOW IT.

36:09.467 --> 36:11.869
BRENNAN, WE CAN'T.

36:11.869 --> 36:14.272
THERE'S NOWHERE
ELSE TO GO, OKAY?

36:14.272 --> 36:17.875
WE NEED TO TRY
AND STOP THIS THING.

36:18.676 --> 36:19.877
MIRANDA!

36:19.877 --> 36:21.078
MIRANDA!

36:21.078 --> 36:22.280
MIRANDA, OPEN THE DOOR.

36:22.680 --> 36:23.881
YOU'RE GONNA DIE IN THERE!

36:24.282 --> 36:27.084
COME ON, MIRANDA!

36:27.084 --> 36:32.690
WHAT IS IT?

36:33.090 --> 36:35.092
IT'S WHAT CREATING YOUR WALL.

36:37.895 --> 36:39.897
YOU KNOW, I GREW UP IN SEATTLE.

36:39.897 --> 36:41.499
I CAN'T BELIEVE I'M
ACTUALLY PRAYING FOR RAIN.

36:41.899 --> 36:43.501
AND RAIN'S JUST A BYPRODUCT.

36:43.501 --> 36:46.304
WHAT WE NEED IS A GOOD
OLD-FASHIONED LIGHTNING STORM.

36:46.304 --> 36:51.909
THUNDER...
AND LIGHTNING.

36:51.909 --> 36:55.112
ALL RIGHT, IT'S TIME.

36:55.513 --> 36:58.716
LET'S FIRE THIS OLD BIRD UP.

37:04.722 --> 37:06.324
IT'S WORKING.

37:06.324 --> 37:08.726
BRING IT ON.

37:08.726 --> 37:09.927
ALL RIGHT.

37:10.328 --> 37:11.929
EVERYBODY DO ME A FAVOUR,
DON'T TOUCH THE HULL.

37:11.929 --> 37:13.931
RIGHT NOW WE'RE PACKING
ABOUT A BILLION VOLTS.

37:14.332 --> 37:17.935
A BILLION, HUH?

37:19.136 --> 37:20.338
COME ON, WE NEED TO STOP IT.

37:20.338 --> 37:21.939
NO.

37:21.939 --> 37:26.744
WAIT...

37:33.951 --> 37:35.953
OF COURSE, IT'D
HAVE ITS OWN PROTECTION.

37:35.953 --> 37:39.957
THAT'S WHAT
HAPPENED TO MY FATHER AND
THE OTHERS, WASN'T IT?

37:41.959 --> 37:43.561
RIGHT THERE... RIGHT THERE.

37:43.561 --> 37:44.762
DON'T MOVE!

37:44.762 --> 37:46.364
OR I'LL SHOOT
HER WHERE SHE STANDS.

37:46.364 --> 37:49.166
COME HERE! COME HERE!

37:50.368 --> 37:51.969
WELL, LET'S GO.

37:51.969 --> 37:55.172
YOU'RE KEEPING EVERYBODY
WAITING FOR THE SHOW.

38:03.180 --> 38:04.782
ADAM, WE HAVE
TO BE POWERED UP BY NOW.

38:04.782 --> 38:06.384
WE'RE GOING TO START
LOSING THE STORM, ADAM.

38:06.384 --> 38:07.585
ALL RIGHT, WE'RE READY.

38:07.585 --> 38:08.786
FIRING AND...

38:09.186 --> 38:10.788
NOW.

38:13.190 --> 38:14.392
IT WON'T WORK, JOSH.

38:14.392 --> 38:15.593
EVERYBODY KNOWS THAT.

38:15.593 --> 38:16.794
YOU CAN'T MAKE THAT GO AWAY.

38:17.194 --> 38:17.995
I DON'T HAVE TO MAKE IT GO AWAY.

38:18.396 --> 38:20.398
I JUST HAVE TO MAKE YOU GO AWAY.

38:21.999 --> 38:26.404
IT'S WORKING.
I CAN SEE THE TOWN.

38:27.204 --> 38:29.206
EMMA, IT'S NOT GOOD ENOUGH.

38:29.206 --> 38:30.408
WE NEED TO TAKE
OUT THE FIELD GENERATOR,

38:30.808 --> 38:32.009
OR IT'S GOING TO POWER
UP AGAIN AND TRAP US INSIDE.

38:32.410 --> 38:33.611
WHAT DO YOU WANT ME TO DO?

38:33.611 --> 38:35.212
I WANT YOU TO KEEP IT FOCUSED
ON THE CENTRE OF THE FIELD.

38:35.212 --> 38:36.414
THAT'S WHERE THE
GENERATOR HAS TO BE.

38:36.814 --> 38:38.015
OKAY.

38:38.015 --> 38:40.418
READY AND FIRING... NOW.

38:43.621 --> 38:46.023
I'M GONNA MISS YOU, MIRANDA.

38:57.635 --> 38:59.637
UGH...

39:31.669 --> 39:33.671
OH, MY GOD.

39:33.671 --> 39:35.272
YOU'RE RIGHT.

39:35.272 --> 39:37.675
THIS CAN'T BE...

39:38.876 --> 39:41.278
UGH...!

39:43.681 --> 39:45.683
NOT THIS TIME, JOSH.

39:53.290 --> 39:56.093
BRENNAN!

40:10.107 --> 40:11.709
WELL, YOU READY?

40:12.109 --> 40:13.310
BRENNAN, I CAN'T.

40:13.711 --> 40:16.113
I'M NOT READY.

40:16.113 --> 40:19.717
WELL, I GUESS I UNDERSTAND.

40:19.717 --> 40:22.520
I MEAN, YOUR WORLD JUST WIDENED
A MILLION TIMES OVER, RIGHT?

40:22.520 --> 40:24.922
STAY WITH ME.

40:24.922 --> 40:28.526
I WISH I COULD,
BUT YOU KNOW I CAN'T.

40:28.926 --> 40:30.528
I HAVE A LIFE.

40:30.528 --> 40:32.129
YOU KNOW, I HAVE
THINGS THAT I HAVE TO DO.

40:32.129 --> 40:35.733
I KNOW.

40:36.133 --> 40:39.336
WELL, WHEN YOU'RE...

40:39.336 --> 40:42.940
WHEN YOU'RE READY
TO SEE MORE OF THE WORLD,

40:42.940 --> 40:44.942
YOU GIVE ME A CALL, HUH.

40:45.342 --> 40:49.747
I WILL.

41:10.167 --> 41:11.769
OH, MAN...

41:11.769 --> 41:13.771
IT'S LIKE GOING FROM
A FISHBOWL TO THE ATLANTIC.

41:13.771 --> 41:15.372
I KIND OF ENVY THEM.

41:15.372 --> 41:17.775
NOW THEY GET A CHANCE
TO EXPERIENCE A FRESH NEW WORLD.

41:18.175 --> 41:19.777
I DON'T KNOW.

41:19.777 --> 41:21.378
I'VE BEEN IN THAT
WORLD MY WHOLE LIFE.

41:21.378 --> 41:25.783
I DON'T KNOW HOW FRESH IT IS.

41:26.984 --> 41:28.586
I'LL SEE YOU SOON.

41:28.586 --> 41:31.789
OKAY.

41:35.392 --> 41:37.394
YOU OKAY?

41:37.394 --> 41:40.197
YEAH.

41:40.598 --> 41:43.801
YEAH, SMALL TOWN
LIVING'S JUST NOT FOR ME.

41:44.201 --> 41:46.604
DIDN'T LOOK LIKE IT
FROM WHERE I WAS STANDING.

41:46.604 --> 41:49.006
YEAH, WELL, IT HAS ITS MOMENTS.

41:49.006 --> 41:50.608
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

41:50.608 --> 41:55.012
I'M NOT VERY
GOOD WITH GOOD-BYES.

42:03.420 --> 42:06.624
LIKE SHAKESPEARE SAID,
"OH, BRAVE NEW WORLD..."

